article.headline: Tulsa 66, UTEP 51
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Ben Uzoh and Rod Earls each scored 10 points to help Tulsa to a 66-51 win over Texas-El Paso on Saturday night. Brett McDade added eight points, while Calvin Walls led the Golden Hurricane with eight rebounds. Tulsa (16-9, 6-6 Conference USA) led 32-18 at halftime and never trailed. They made only 38 percent of their shots but UTEP's shooting was even worse. For the game, The Miners (13-13, 5-7) hit only 25 percent of their shots from the field. Kevin Henderson led UTEP with 14 points and six rebounds. He was 7-of-9 from the free throw line. Maurice Thomas added 10 points. Tulsa outrebounded UTEP 49-35.
